5 Subject: Education; retirement; Vermont State Teachers’ Retirement System
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to extend the
7 provision authorizing a beneficiary of the Vermont State Teachers’ Retirement
8 System to resume service as an interim educator and continue to receive a
9 retirement allowance for that period.
10 An act relating to the retirement allowance for interim educators
11 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
12 Sec. 1. 2022 Acts and Resolves No. 173, Sec. 1 is amended to read:
13 Sec. 1. FY 2023; RESTORATION OF SERVICE; VERMONT STATE
14 TEACHERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM
15 (a) Authority. Notwithstanding 16 V.S.A. § 1939 or any other provision of
16 law, in fiscal year 2023, a beneficiary who retired from the System as a
17 Group A or a Group C member may resume service, as that term is defined in
18 16 V.S.A. § 1931, to serve as an interim school educator for a period not to
19 exceed one school year and receive the beneficiary’s retirement allowance for
20 the entire period that service is resumed, provided that:
